==English==

===Noun===

'''[[country]] [[pop]]'''

# (''descriptive'') A [[subgenre]] of [[country music]], blending the sounds of the [[Nashville sound]] and [[popular music]]; produced and marketed to reach a wide audience.
# (''derogatory'') Derogatory reference to a type of country music that some [[critic]]s believe sounds more like popular music than traditional forms of country (e.g., [[honky tonk]]); a catch-all term referring to country music produced after 1990 (when artists such as Garth Brooks, Tim McGraw and Faith HIll rose to fame).